NET text notes (Accordance): "There is some textual debate about the legitimacy of this expression here. The text reads merely day (, yom). BHS suggests the word is to be deleted as a dittography of the plural ending of the preceding word. The word is in the Greek and Latin, and the Syriac represents the typical idiom day after day as though the noun were repeated. Either  has dropped out by haplography or a  (mem) has been left out, i.e., reading  (yomam, daily).
